#: src/gui-gtk4/uifiles/icc_gamut_dialog.ui:26
msgid ""
"This image shows a comparison of the various working gamuts available in "
"Siril. (Note P3 is not available in Siril: it is shown for reference, and "
"you can provide a P3 ICC profile if desired.)\n"
"    The CIE1931 xy space represents all the colors visible to human "
"eyesight.\n"
"    sRGB is a standard for web publication and corresponds to the gamut of "
"most monitors.\n"
"    Other color spaces offer larger gamuts covering more of the CIE1931 "
"space. Rec2020 has the largest gamut that does not include imaginary colors; "
"ProPhoto RGB has an even larger gamut especially in the green / blue region, "
"but does include some imaginary colors.\n"
"    Printed photographs can offer richer, deeper colors if produced from a "
"color space with a larger gamut. Specialist monitors are also available with "
"larger gamuts than sRGB, and you will probably want to use a gamut at least "
"as large as your monitor can display."
msgstr ""

